<%- include('../../partials/implementer-core.md.ejs', { specificsBlock: `## C# / ASP.NET Core Specifics

### API Patterns
- Prefer Minimal APIs (\`app.MapGet\`, \`app.MapPost\`) for new .NET 6+ projects; use controllers only when the project already uses them.
- Validate request models with \`FluentValidation\` or Data Annotations; register validators via DI.
- Return \`Results.Ok(dto)\` / \`Results.Problem(...)\` from Minimal API handlers — never raw \`object\`.
- Use record types for DTOs: \`record CreateUserRequest(string Name, string Email)\`.

### Dependency Injection
- Register all services in \`Program.cs\` via \`builder.Services\`; scope lifetime correctly (Singleton / Scoped / Transient).
- Never use the Service Locator pattern — inject dependencies via constructor parameters.

### Testing
- Use \`xUnit\` with \`WebApplicationFactory<Program>\` for integration tests against the real DI container.
- Use \`Moq\` or \`NSubstitute\` for mocking dependencies in unit tests.
- Avoid LINQ pitfalls in tests: materialize queries with \`ToList()\` before asserting.

### Anti-patterns to avoid
- Never use \`dynamic\` or unconstrained \`object\` — define explicit types.
- Never call \`.Result\` or \`.Wait()\` on \`Task\` — always \`await\`.
- Never catch \`Exception\` without rethrowing or logging with structured context.
- Never mutate shared state in \`Singleton\`-scoped services without thread-safety.
- Never expose EF Core entities directly as API responses — map to DTOs.` }) %>
